"smart_sources:000 Zettelkasten/Expressing chemokine receptors on CAR-T cells that match and respond to tumour-derived chemokines alleviates cell trafficking issues to the desired location..md": {"path":"000 Zettelkasten/Expressing chemokine receptors on CAR-T cells that match and respond to tumour-derived chemokines alleviates cell trafficking issues to the desired location..md","class_name":"SmartSource","history":[{"blocks":{"000 Zettelkasten/Expressing chemokine receptors on CAR-T cells that match and respond to tumour-derived chemokines alleviates cell trafficking issues to the desired location..md#":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Expressing chemokine receptors on CAR-T cells that match and respond to tumour-derived chemokines alleviates cell trafficking issues to the desired location..md#Expressing chemokine receptors on CAR-T cells that match and respond to tumour-derived chemokines alleviates cell trafficking issues to the desired location. One such example is the use of fibroblast activation protein (FAP)-targeted CAR-T cells, an antigen expressed in the microenvironment of different types of solid neoplasms. A monoclonal antibody targeting this protein was successful in both mice and non-human primates in localizing to solid tumour targets while sparing healthy tissue. Otherwise, [[Local administration of CAR T-cells into the region of a solid tumour targets remaining tumourigenic cells and reduces adverse responses in healthy tissue.]]{1}":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Expressing chemokine receptors on CAR-T cells that match and respond to tumour-derived chemokines alleviates cell trafficking issues to the desired location..md#References":true},"mtime":1709479487287,"size":832,"hash":"bcdc4e00de0af19fbfee8e5a251838d9f4c855bb0657ed6ad7a4cd3684c94dbe"}],"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.00374009,-0.00393268,-0.02516817,0.03921484,0.04039944,-0.00803383,0.01803681,-0.02992178,-0.0101494,0.00031415,-0.00888667,-0.03453226,-0.02852265,-0.04866173,0.03348438,-0